msgstr ""
"<p><big><b>Pengaturan Keamanan Lainnya</b></big></P>\n"
"<p>Dalam dialog ini, ganti aneka pengaturan yang terkait dengan keamanan "
"lokal.</p>"

#. Misc dialog help 2/14
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:173
msgid ""
"<p><b>File Permissions</b>: Settings for the permissions\n"
"of certain system files are set according to the data in /etc/permissions."
"secure\n"
"or /etc/permissions.easy. Which file is used depends on this selection.\n"
"Launching SuSEconfig sets these permissions according to /etc/permissions."
"*.\n"
"This fixes files with incorrect permissions, whether this occurred "
"accidentally\n"
"or by intruders.</p><p>\n"
"With <b>Easy</b>, most of the system files that are only readable by root\n"
"in Secure are modified so other users can also read these files.\n"
"Using <b>Secure</b>, certain system files, such as /var/log/messages, can "
"only\n"
"be viewed by the user root. Some programs can only be launched by root or "
"by\n"
"daemons, not by ordinary users.\n"
"The most secure setting is <b>Paranoid</B>. With it, you must\n"
"decide which users are able to run X applications and setuid programs.</p>\n"
msgstr ""
"<p><b>Hak Akses Berkas</b>: Pengaturan untuk perizinan berkas sistem\n"
"tertentu diatur sesuai dengan data di /etc/permissions.secure atau\n"
"/etc/permissions.easy. Berkas mana yang digunakan tergantung dari pilihan "
"ini.\n"
"Peluncuran SuSEconfig mengatur izin ini sesuai dengan /etc/permissions.*.\n"
"Ini memperbaiki berkas dengan izin yang salah, apakah ini terjadi secara "
"tidak sengaja\n"
"atau oleh penyusup</p><p>\n"
"Dengan <b>Mudah</b>, sebagian besar berkas sistem yang hanya dapat dibaca "
"oleh root\n"
"di Aman dimodifikasi sehingga pengguna lain juga bisa membaca berkas-berkas "
"ini.\n"
"Dengan menggunakan <b>Aman</b>, file sistem tertentu, seperti /var/log/"
"messages\n"
"hanya dapat dilihat oleh root pengguna. Beberapa program hanya bisa "
"diluncurkan oleh\n"
"root atau oleh daemon, bukan oleh pengguna biasa.\n"
"Pengaturan yang paling aman adalah <b>Paranoid</B>. Dengan itu, Anda harus\n"
"memutuskan pengguna mana yang dapat menjalankan aplikasi X dan program "
"setuid.</p>\n"

#. Misc dialog help 6/14
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:189
msgid ""
"<p><b>User Launching updatedb</b>: The program updatedb runs \n"
"once a day. It scans your entire file system and creates a database "
"(locatedb)\n"
"that stores the location of every file. The database can be searched by the\n"
"program \"locate\".  Here, set the user that runs this command: <b>nobody</"
"b>\n"
"    (few files) or <b>root</b> (all files).</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p><b>Peluncuran Pengguna updatedb</b>: Program updatedb berjalan sekali\n"
"sehari. Ini memindai seluruh sistem berkas Anda dan membuat basis data "
"(locatedb)\n"
"yang menyimpan lokasi setiap berkas. Basis data dapat dicari dengan program "
"\"locate\".\n"
"Di sini, atur pengguna yang menjalankan perintah ini: <b>nobody</b>\n"
"    (beberapa berkas) atau <b>root</b> (semua berkas).</p>"

#. Misc dialog help 10/14
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:197
msgid ""
"<p><b>Current Directory in root's Path</b> On a DOS system,\n"
"the system first searches for executable files (programs) in the current\n"
"directory then in the current path variable. In contrast, a UNIX-like "
"system\n"
"searches for them exclusively via the search path (variable PATH).</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p><b>Direktori Saat ini pada path root</b> Pada sistem DOS,\n"
"sistem pertama mencari berkas executable (program) di direktori saat ini\n"
"lalu pada variabel path saat ini. Sebaliknya, sistem mirip UNIX mencarinya\n"
"secara eksklusif melalui path pencarian (variabel PATH).</p>"

#. Misc dialog help 11/14
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:204
msgid ""
"<p><b>Current Directory in the Path of Regular Users</b><br> A DOS\n"
"system first searches for executable files (programs) in the current "
"directory\n"
"then in the current path variable. In contrast, a UNIX-like system searches\n"
"for them exclusively via the search path (variable PATH).</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p><b>Direktori Saat Ini di Path Pengguna Reguler</b><br> Sistem DOS\n"
"pertama mencari berkas yang dapat dieksekusi (program) di direktori saat "
"ini,\n"
"lalu di variabel path saat ini. Sebaliknya, sistem mirip UNIX mencari "
"mereka\n"
"secara eksklusif melalui path pencarian (variabel PATH). </p>"

#. Misc dialog help 12/14
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:211
msgid ""
"<p>Some systems set up a work-around by adding the dot (\".\") to the\n"
"search path, enabling files in the current path to be found and executed.\n"
"This is highly dangerous because you may accidentally launch unknown "
"programs in\n"
"the current directory instead of the usual systemwide files. As a result,\n"
"executing <i>Trojan Horses</i>, which exploit this weakness and invade your "
"system,\n"
"is rather easy if you set this option.</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>Beberapa sistem mengatur pekerjaan-sekitar dengan menambahkan titik (\"."
"\") ke\n"
"path pencarian, memungkinkan berkas di path saat ini dapat ditemukan dan "
"dieksekusi.\n"
"Ini sangat berbahaya karena Anda mungkin secara tidak sengaja meluncurkan "
"program yang\n"
"tidak dikenal di direktori saat ini, bukan berkas systemwide yang biasa. "
"Akibatnya, mengeksekusi\n"
"<i>Kuda Troya</i>, yang mengeksploitasi kelemahan ini dan menyerang sistem "
"Anda, agak mudah\n"
"jika Anda menetapkan opsi ini. </p>"

#. Misc dialog help 13/14
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:220
msgid ""
"<p>\"yes\": the dot (\".\") is attached to the end of the search\n"
"path of root, making it the last to be searched.</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>\"ya\": titik (\".\") dilekatkan pada ujung path pencarian root,\n"
"menjadikannya yang terakhir dicari.</p>"

#. Misc dialog help 14/14
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:224
msgid ""
"<p>\"no\": the user root always must launch programs in the\n"
"current directory prefixed with a \"./\". Example: \"./configure\".</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>\"tidak\": root pengguna selalu harus meluncurkan program di\n"
"direktori saat ini diawali dengan \"./\". Contoh: \"./configure\".</p>"

#. Misc dialog help 14/14
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:228
msgid ""
"<p><b>Enable Magic SysRq Keys</b><br> If you check this option, you\n"
"will have some control over the system even if it crashes (for example, "
"during kernel\n"
"debugging). For details, see /usr/src/linux/Documentation/sysrq.txt</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p><b>Aktifkan Tombol Magic SysRq</b><br> Jika Anda memeriksa opsi ini, "
"Anda\n"
"akan memiliki kontrol atas sistem ini bahkan jika macet (misalnya saat "
"awakutu kernel).\n"
"Untuk detailnya, lihat /usr/src/linux/Documentation/sysrq.txt </p>"

#. help text: security overview dialog 1/
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:234
msgid ""
"<P><B>Security Overview</B><BR>This overview shows the most important "
"security settings.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P><B>Ikhtisar Keamanan</B><BR>Ikhtisar ini menunjukkan pengaturan keamanan "
"yang paling penting.</P>"

#. help text: security overview dialog 1/
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:238
msgid ""
"<P>To change the current value, click the link associated to the option.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Untuk mengubah nilai saat ini, klik tautan yang terkait dengan pilihan "
"tersebut.</P>"

#. help text: security overview dialog 1/
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:242
msgid ""
"<P> A check mark in the <B>Security Status</B> column means that the current "
"value of the option is secure.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P> Tanda centang di kolom <B>Status Keamanan</B> berarti nilai opsi saat "
"ini aman.</P>"

#. an error message (rich text)
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:246
msgid ""
"<P><B>The current value could not be read. The service is probably not "
"installed or the option is missing on the system.</B></P>"
msgstr ""
"<P><B>Nilai saat ini tidak dapat dibaca. Layanan ini mungkin tidak terpasang "
"atau pilihannya hilang pada sistem.</B></P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:252
msgid ""
"<P>A display manager provides a graphical login screen and can be accessed\n"
"across the network by an X server running on another system if so\n"
"configured.</P><P>The windows that are being displayed would then transmit\n"
"their data across the network. If that network is not fully trusted, then "
"the\n"
"network traffic can be eavesdropped by an attacker, gaining access not only "
"to\n"
"the graphical content of the display, but also to usernames and passwords "
"that\n"
"are being used.</P><P>If you do not need <EM>XDMCP</EM> for remote "
"graphical\n"
"logins, then disable this option.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Pengelola tampilan menyediakan layar log masuk grafis dan dapat diakses "
"di\n"
"seluruh jaringan oleh peladen X yang berjalan pada sistem lain jika "
"dikonfigurasi dengan\n"
"benar.</P><P>Jendela yang dipajang kemudian akan mengirimkan data mereka ke "
"seluruh\n"
"jaringan. Jika jaringan itu tidak sepenuhnya dipercaya, maka lalu lintas "
"jaringan dapat diperbarui\n"
"oleh penyerang, mendapatkan akses tidak hanya ke konten grafis layar, tetapi "
"juga untuk nama\n"
"pengguna dan kata kunci yang sedang digunakan.</P> <P> Jika Anda tidak "
"memerlukan <EM>XDMCP</EM>\n"
"untuk log masuk grafis jauh, nonaktifkan opsi ini.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:262
msgid ""
"<P>Malfunctions in a system are usually detected by anomalies in its "
"behaviour. Syslog messages about events that reoccur on a regular basis are "
"important to find causes of problems. And the absence of a single record can "
"tell more than the absence of all log records.</P><P>Therefore, syslog "
"messages of system events are only useful if they are present.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Malfungsi dalam sistem biasanya terdeteksi oleh anomali dalam "
"perilakunya. Pesan syslog tentang kejadian yang berulang secara berkala "
"penting untuk menemukan penyebab masalah. Dan tidak adanya satu record pun "
"bisa diceritakan lebih banyak daripada tidak adanya semua catatan log.</"
"P><P>Oleh karena itu, pesan syslog dari kejadian sistem hanya berguna jika "
"ada.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:265
msgid ""
"<P>Chroot execution environments restrict a process to only access files "
"that it needs by placing them in a separate subdirectory and running the "
"process with a changed root (chroot) set to that directory.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Lingkungan eksekusi chroot membatasi proses untuk hanya mengakses berkas "
"yang dibutuhkannya dengan menempatkannya di subdirektori terpisah dan "
"menjalankan proses dengan root yang telah diubah (chroot) yang diset ke "
"direktori tersebut.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:268
msgid ""
"<P>The DHCP client daemon should run as the user <EM>dhcpd</EM> to minimize "
"a possible threat if the service is found vulnerable to a weakness in its "
"program code.</P><P>Note that dhcpd must never run as <EM>root</EM> or with "
"the <EM>CAP_SYS_CHROOT</EM> capability for the chroot execution confinement "
"to be effective.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Daemon klien DHCP harus dijalankan sebagai pengguna <EM>dhcpd</EM> untuk "
"meminimalkan kemungkinan ancaman jika layanan ditemukan rentan terhadap "
"kelemahan dalam kode programnya.</P><P>Perhatikan bahwa dhcpd harus tidak "
"pernah menjalankan <EM>root</EM> atau dengan kemampuan <EM>CAP_SYS_CHROOT</"
"EM> agar pengurungan eksekusi chroot menjadi efektif.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:271
msgid ""
"<P>Administrators should never log on as <EM>root</EM> into an X Window "
"session to minimize the usage of the root privileges.</P><P>This option does "
"not help against careless administrators, but shall prevent attackers to be "
"able to log on as <EM>root</EM> via the display manager if they guess or "
"otherwise acquire the password.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Administrator tidak boleh log masuk sebagai <EM>root</EM> ke dalam sesi "
"jendela X untuk meminimalkan penggunaan hak istimewa root.</P><P>Pilihan ini "
"tidak membantu administrator yang ceroboh, namun harus mencegah penyerang "
"untuk dapat masuk sebagai <EM>root</EM> melalui pengelola tampilan jika "
"mereka menebak atau mendapatkan kata sandinya.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:274
msgid ""
"<P>X Window clients, e.g. programs that open a window on your display, "
"connect\n"
"to the X server that runs on the physical machine. Programs can also run on "
"a\n"
"different system and display their content on the X server through network\n"
"connections.</P><P>When enabled, the X server listens on a port 6000 plus "
"the\n"
"display number. Since network traffic is transferred unencrypted and "
"therefore\n"
"subject to network sniffing, and since the port held open by the X server\n"
"offers attack options, the secure setting is to disable it.</P><P>To display "
"X\n"
"Window clients across a network, we recommend the use of secure shell "
"(<EM>ssh</EM>), which allows the X Window clients to connect to the X server "
"through the encrypted ssh connection.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Klien Jendela X Window, mis. Program yang membuka jendela pada layar "
"Anda,\n"
"terhubung ke peladen X yang berjalan pada mesin fisik. Program juga dapat "
"berjalan pada\n"
"sistem yang berbeda dan menampilkan konten mereka di peladen X melalui "
"koneksi\n"
"jaringan.</P><P>Bila diaktifkan, peladen X mendengarkan port 6000 plus nomor "
"tampilan.\n"
"Karena lalu lintas jaringan yang ditransfer tidak terenkripsi dan oleh "
"karena itu tunduk pada\n"
"sniffing jaringan, dan karena port yang dibuka oleh peladen X menawarkan "
"pilihan serangan,\n"
"pengaturan amannya adalah untuk menonaktifkannya.\n"
"</P><P>Untuk menampilkan klien Jendela X\n"
"di seluruh jaringan, kami merekomendasikan penggunaan shell aman (<EM>ssh</"
"EM>), yang memungkinkan klien Jendela X terhubung ke peladen X melalui "
"koneksi ssh yang terenkripsi.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:284
msgid ""
"<P>The email delivery subsystem is always started. However, it does not "
"expose\n"
"itself outside the system by default, since it does not listen on the SMTP "
"network port 25.</P><P>If you do not deliver emails to your system through "
"the SMTP protocol, then disable this option.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Subsistem pengiriman surel selalu dimulai. Namun, itu tidak mengekspos\n"
"dirinya sendiri di luar sistem secara bawaan, karena tidak mendengarkan pada "
"port jaringan SMTP 25</P><P>Jika Anda tidak mengirimkan surel ke sistem Anda "
"melalui protokol SMTP, maka nonaktifkan opsi ini.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:287
msgid ""
"<P>If a package containing a service that is currently running is being\n"
"updated, the service is restarted after the files in the package have been\n"
"installed.</P><P>This makes sense in most cases, and it is safe to do,\n"
"considering that many services either need their binaries or configuration\n"
"files accessible in the file system. Otherwise these services would "
"continue\n"
"to run until the services are stopped, e.g. running daemons are\n"
"killed.</P><P>This setting should only be changed if there is a specific\n"
"reason to do so.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Jika paket yang berisi layanan yang sedang berjalan sedang\n"
"diperbarui, layanan akan dimulai ulang setelah berkas dalam paket\n"
"terpasang.</P><P>Ini masuk akal dalam banyak kasus, dan aman untuk "
"dilakukan,\n"
"mengingat banyak layanan memerlukan binari atau konfigurasi yang dapat "
"diakses\n"
"di sistem berkas. Jika tidak, layanan ini akan terus berjalan sampai layanan "
"dihentikan, mis.\n"
"menjalankan daemon yang dibunuh.</P><P>Pengaturan ini hanya boleh diubah "
"jika ada alasan\n"
"khusus untuk melakukannya.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:297
msgid ""
"<P>If a package containing a service that is currently running is being\n"
"uninstalled, the service is stopped before the files of the package are\n"
"removed.</P><P>This makes sense in most cases, and it is safe to do,\n"
"considering that many services either need their binaries or configuration\n"
"files accessible in the file system. Otherwise these services would "
"continue\n"
"to run until they are stopped, e.g. running daemons are\n"
"killed.</P><P>This setting should only be changed if there is a specific\n"
"reason to do so.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Jika paket yang berisi layanan yang saat ini berjalan sedang\n"
"dihapus, layanan dihentikan sebelum berkas paket\n"
"dihapus.</P><P>Ini masuk akal dalam banyak kasus, dan ini aman dilakukan.\n"
"Mengingat banyak layanan memerlukan binari atau berkas konfigurasi yang "
"dapat diakses\n"
"di sistem berkas. Jika tidak, layanan ini akan terus berjalan sampai "
"dihentikan, mis.\n"
"menjalankan daemon yang dibunuh.</P><P>Pengaturan ini hanya boleh diubah "
"jika ada alasan\n"
"khusus untuk melakukannya.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:307
msgid ""
"<P>A system can be overwhelmed with numerous connection attempts so that the "
"system runs out of memory, leading to a Denial of Service (DoS) "
"vulnerability.</P><P>The use of syncookies is a method that can help in such "
"situations. But in configurations with a very large number of legitimate "
"connection attempts from one source, the <EM>Enabled</EM> setting can cause "
"problems with denied TCP connections under high load.</P><P>Still, for most "
"environments, syncookies are the first line of defense against SYN flood DoS "
"attacks, so the secure setting is <EM>Enabled</EM>.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Sebuah sistem dapat terbebani dengan banyak upaya koneksi sehingga sistem "
"kehabisan memori, menyebabkan kerentanan Denial of Service (DoS).</"
"P><P>Penggunaan syncookies adalah metode yang dapat membantu dalam situasi "
"seperti itu. Tetapi dalam konfigurasi dengan sejumlah besar upaya koneksi "
"yang sah dari satu sumber, pengaturan yang <EM>Diaktifkan</EM> dapat "
"menyebabkan masalah dengan koneksi TCP yang ditolak di bawah beban tinggi.</"
"P><P>Namun, untuk sebagian besar lingkungan, syncookies adalah garis "
"pertahanan pertama melawan serangan SYN flood DoS, jadi pengaturan amannya "
"adalah <EM>Diaktifkan</EM>.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:310 src/include/security/helps.rb:314
msgid ""
"<P>IP forwarding means to pass on network packets that have been received, "
"but that are not destined for one of the system's configured network "
"interfaces, e.g. network interface addresses.</P><P>If a system forwards "
"network traffic on ISO/OSI layer 3, it is called a router. If you do not "
"need that routing functionality, then disable this option.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>IP forwarding berarti meneruskan paket jaringan yang telah diterima, "
"namun tidak ditujukan untuk salah satu antarmuka jaringan yang dikonfigurasi "
"oleh sistem, mis. alamat antarmuka jaringan.</P><P>Jika sistem meneruskan "
"lalu lintas jaringan pada layer ISO/OSI 3, maka disebut router. Jika Anda "
"tidak memerlukan fungsi routing itu, maka nonaktifkan opsi ini.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:313
msgid "<P>This setting applies to <EM>IPv4</EM> only.</P>"
msgstr "<P> Pengaturan ini hanya berlaku untuk <EM>IPv4</EM>.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:317
msgid "<P>This setting applies to <EM>IPv6</EM> only.</P>"
msgstr "<P> Pengaturan ini hanya berlaku untuk <EM>IPv6</EM>.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:318
msgid ""
"<P>Magic SysRq Keys enable some control over the system even if it crashes "
"(e.g. during kernel debugging) or if the system does not respond.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Tombol Magic SysRq mengaktifkan beberapa kontrol atas sistem bahkan jika "
"macet (misal saat awakutu kernel) atau jika sistem tidak merespons.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:321
msgid ""
"<P>There are predefined file permissions in /etc/permissions.* files. The "
"most restrictive file permissions are defined 'secure' or 'paranoid' file.</"
"P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Ada hak akses berkas yang telah ditentukan di berkas /etc/permissions.*. "
"Izin berkas yang paling ketat didefinisikan sebagai berkas 'aman' atau "
"'paranoid'.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:324
msgid ""
"<P>Basic system services must be enabled to provide system consistency and "
"to run the security-related services.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Layanan sistem dasar harus diaktifkan untuk memberikan konsistensi sistem "
"dan menjalankan layanan terkait keamanan.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:327
msgid ""
"<P>Every running service is a potential target of a security attack. "
"Therefore it is recommended to turn off all services which are not used by "
"the system.</P>"
msgstr ""
"<P>Setiap layanan yang berjalan merupakan target potensial serangan "
"keamanan. Oleh karena itu dianjurkan untuk mematikan semua layanan yang "
"tidak digunakan oleh sistem.</P>"

#: src/include/security/helps.rb:334
msgid ""
"<p><b><big>Boot Security</big></b></p>\n"
"<p>In this dialog, change various boot settings related to security.</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p><b><big>Keamanan Boot</big></b></p>\n"
"<p>Dalam dialog ini, ubah berbagai pengaturan boot yang terkait dengan "
"keamanan.</p>"

#. TRANSLATORS: part of help text - default action (the default is
#. reboot)
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:341
msgid ""
"Usually the system reboots. Sometimes it is desirable\n"
"to ignore this event, for example, when the system serves as both\n"
"workstation and server."
msgstr ""
"Biasanya mulai ulang sistem. Terkadang sangat disesalkan untuk\n"
"mengabaikan event ini, misalnya saat sistem berfungsi baik sebagai\n"
"workstation maupun peladen."

#. TRANSLATORS: part of help text - default action (the default is halt)
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:348
msgid ""
"By default the system halts but sometimes it is desirable\n"
"to ignore this event, for example, when the system serves as both\n"
"workstation and server."
msgstr ""
"Secara bawaan sistem berhenti tapi kadang kala diinginkan untuk\n"
"mengabaikan event ini, misalnya saat sistem berfungsi sebagai\n"
"workstation dan peladen."

#. Boot dialog help 2/4
#. TRANSLATORS: %s is help text - default action
#: src/include/security/helps.rb:357
#, c-format
msgid ""
"<p><b>Interpretation of Ctrl + Alt + Del</b>:\n"
"Configure what the system should do in response to\n"
"someone at the console pressing the CTRL + ALT + DEL key\n"
"combination. %s</p>"
